'Quite right quite right , said the little man . 
'With which view , continued Mr. Pickwick , 'I made use of the argument which my experience of men has taught me is the most likely to succeed in any case . 
'Ay , ay , said the little man , 'very good , very good , indeed but you should have suggested it to me . 
My dear sir , I'm quite certain you cannot be ignorant of the extent of confidence which must be placed in professional men . 
Hows'ever , that's neither here nor there . 
You want me to accept of half a guinea . 
Then the next question is , what the devil do you want with me , as the man said , wen he see the ghost ? 'We want to know said Mr. Wardle . 
