It's a distressing case very I never knew one more so but really , my dear sir , really we have no power to control this lady's actions . 
I warned you before we came , my dear sir , that there was nothing to look to but a compromise . 
There was a short pause . 
'What kind of compromise would you recommend ? inquired Mr. Pickwick . 
'Why , my dear Sir , our friend's in an unpleasant position very much so . 
We must be content to suffer some pecuniary loss . 
'I'll suffer any , rather than submit to this disgrace , and let her , fool as she is , be made miserable for life , said Wardle . 
'I rather think it can be done , said the bustling little man . 
Jingle , will you step with us into the next room for a moment ? Mr. Jingle assented , and the quartette walked into an empty apartment . 
Don't frown , Sir , don't frown I say , between you and I , WE know it . 
'Very good , very good , said the little man , observing the impression he had made . 
'Now , the fact is , that beyond a few hundreds , the lady has little or nothing till the death of her mother fine old lady , my dear Sir . 
