'Fact , Sir , said Mr. Weller 'if they was gen'l'm'n , you'd call 'em misanthropes , but as it is , they only takes to pike keepin' . 
With such conversation , possessing the inestimable charm of blending amusement with instruction , did Mr. Weller beguile the tediousness of the journey , during the greater part of the day . 
The Great White Horse is famous in the neighbourhood , in the same degree as a prize ox , or a county paper chronicled turnip , or unwieldy pig for its enormous size . 
'Do you stop here , sir ? 'I do , said Mr. Pickwick . 
'Dear me , said Mr. Magnus , 'I never knew anything like these extraordinary coincidences . 
Why , I stop here too . 
I hope we dine together ? 'With pleasure , replied Mr. Pickwick . 
'I am not quite certain whether I have any friends here or not , though . 
'No ! 'Nor Winkle ? 'No ! 'My friends have not arrived to day , Sir , said Mr. Pickwick . 
'We will dine alone , then . 
Show us a private room , waiter . 
Mr. Peter Magnus was naturally of a very communicative disposition , and the brandy and water operated with wonderful effect in warming into life the deepest hidden secrets of his bosom . 
'Partly right , Sir , replied Mr. Peter Magnus , 'but partly wrong at the same time try again , Mr. Pickwick . 
'Ah ! said Mr. Magnus . 
