And the learned gentleman , with a firm and steady frown , placed his hands on his hips , and smiled suspiciously to the jury . 
On this question there arose the edifying brow beating , customary on such points . 
First of all , Mr. Winkle said it was quite impossible for him to say how many times he had seen Mrs. Bardell . 
Then he was asked if he had seen her twenty times , to which he replied , 'Certainly more than that . 
'Were you accompanied on that occasion by a friend of the name of Tupman , and another by the name of Snodgrass ? 'Yes , I was . 
