Breakfast had scarcely been cleared away on the succeeding morning , when a waiter brought in Mr. Dowler's card , with a request to be allowed permission to introduce a friend . 
Mr. Dowler at once followed up the delivery of the card , by bringing himself and the friend also . 
He had a gold watch , and a gold curb chain with large gold seals and he carried a pliant ebony cane with a gold top . 
His linen was of the very whitest , finest , and stiffest his wig of the glossiest , blackest , and curliest . 
His snuff was princes' mixture his scent BOUQUET DU ROI . 
His features were contracted into a perpetual smile and his teeth were in such perfect order that it was difficult at a small distance to tell the real from the false . 
