This broke up the party . 
So , after taking a glass of soda water and brandy at the bar , he turned into the coffee room , dispirited rather than elevated by the occurrences of the evening . 
Sitting in front of the fire , with his back towards him , was a tallish gentleman in a greatcoat the only other occupant of the room . 
It was rather a cool evening for the season of the year , and the gentleman drew his chair aside to afford the new comer a sight of the fire . 
He had made one step towards it , before he checked himself . 
As he did so , Mr. Dowler very hastily drew back . 
A blow ! Never ! said Mr. Dowler , looking meeker than Mr. Winkle had expected in a gentleman of his ferocity . 
