'Wot a thing it is to be so sought arter ! observed Sam , smiling . 
'I don't take no pride out on it , Sammy , replied Mr. Weller , poking the fire vehemently , 'it's a horrid sitiwation . 
I'm actiwally drove out o' house and home by it . 
'How are you safer there than anyveres else ? interrupted Sam . 
Cos a coachman's a privileged indiwidual , replied Mr. Weller , looking fixedly at his son . 
And wot other man can say the same , Sammy ? 'Vell , there's somethin' in that , said Sam . 
